Content: What happens when motion capture, machine learning, and creative minds collide? The "Duets on AI and Dance" workshop at NYU Shanghai explored how human and machine perspectives can interact, coexist, and occasionally conflict within the context of dance. The event was led by Prof. Jung Hyun Moon from Interactive Media Arts (IMA) and Prof. Siye Tao from Performing Arts. We asked NYU Shanghai students to share photos from their travels during the fall semester and loved how Audrey Merchak captured Suzhou and Shanghai with a nostalgic serenity.

In a unique workshop inspired by the NYU Shanghai course Good Death: China and Comparative Perspectives, students and faculty visited Shanghai Fushou Garden to reflect on life’s profound questions. Through meditation walks, honoring influential figures, and posting their wishes, participants discovered new perspectives on living meaningfully and embracing the present.
